ROCm decode: fuse router_select + HC expand hotspots

Status: proposed optimization plan from 2026-05-09 decode profile (codex high-reasoning analysis at /tmp/codex_advice.log).

Goal: recover the largest part of the 27 ms/tok currently spent in router_select, matmul_q8_0_hc_expand, and attention_output_low_q8 on gfx1151. Decode wall 71 ms/tok; target 220 GB/s ceiling = ~43 ms/tok = 23 t/s.

Chosen highest-ROI approach (in order):

1. router_select (saves ~7-9 ms/tok). Replace decode router softplus + serial select with one fused 256-thread block kernel rocm_router_softplus_select_one_kernel. Each thread computes probs[e] = sqrt(softplus(logits[e])), writes probs (debug/test path still reads it), then block-reduces top-6 using wave32 __shfl_down argmax + 8-entry shared wave summary. Tie-break: lower index wins (matches existing serial > comparison). Hash-mode and bias-mode preserved. Same fusion pattern for batch wrapper (one block per token, grid=n_tokens, block=256). Sketch in /tmp/codex_advice.log lines 1404-1500. Expected per-call: 244 us -> 25-60 us in SYNC_EACH.

2. matmul_q8_0_hc_expand (saves ~6-8 ms/tok). Fuse HC expand into the Q8 producer kernel for the two composed wrappers ds4_metal_matmul_q8_0_hc_expand_tensor (3325) and ds4_metal_shared_down_hc_expand_q8_0_tensor (3346). Lane 0 of each Q8 output-row wave already stores block_out[d]; have it also load residual_hc[d, 0..3] and split (post[4]+comb[4*4]) and write the four HC rows immediately. Keep block_out store for ABI/debug. Safe because both wrappers already do matmul-then-expand sequentially with no intervening consumer. New macro ROCM_DEFINE_MATMUL_Q8_0_HC_EXPAND(NROWS, HAS_ADD); fall back to current path when n_hc != 4, n_tok != 1, in_dim % 32 != 0. Sketch in /tmp/codex_advice.log lines 1528-1591.

3. attention_output_low_q8 (deprioritized, ~1 ms/tok possible). Already at ~195 GB/s vs 220 ceiling; current wave-per-row kernel is bandwidth-bound. Optional: production-shape specialization for group_dim=4096, rank=1024, n_groups=8, qblocks=128, row_bytes=4352 to let compiler unroll fixed loops. Defer until after items 1 and 2 land.

